The Clerk of the Edo State House of Assembly, Yahaya Ogmobai, yesterday swore in two members-elect who were not part of the nine that took their oath last week. The members-elect sworn-in were Emmanuel Okoduwa representing Esan North East I, and Ojezele Sunday representing Esan South East constituency of the state. Nine out of 24 members-elect of the assembly were on June 17 sworn-in by the clerk. Daily Trust reports that yesterday’s swearing-in brought to 13, the total number of lawmakers who have been inaugurated while 13 members-elect were yet to be sworn-in. Edo: Two new members-elect take oath of office Oyegun: APC may lose 2020 governorship election in Edo if... APC may lose 2020 gov’ship election in Edo — Oyegun Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin